laboratory_examinations.findings: The liver is normal in size, echogenicity, and architecture. There is no focal liver lesion. The gallbladder wall is edematous and there is a wall echo shadow sign indicating it is filled with stones. There is no intra- or extra-hepatic biliary ductal dilatation and the common bile duct measures 4 mm. The visualized pancreas is normal.
